result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Mona Ann Rolbiecki was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Mona Ann Rolbiecki in court with attorney Joseph James Dorlack.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant entered a guilty plea as to count 1. Count 2 is dismissed and read-in. Count 3 is dismissed outright. Court imposed the following sentence:

     The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

 

4 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 1 day)
  -  2  YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2  YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  

FINE: $1850.00  APPLY ANY BAIL THAT IS POSTED and refund the balance. 

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00, to be paid at $/month consecutive to payment of fine or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of surcharge.

D/L REVOCATION: 36 months;

IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months;

Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel on: 06/22/2016. Defendant to serve 30 days huber, consecutive, as penalty for failure to attend Victim Impact Panel.

Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;

DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
 
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00  paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to City of Oconomowoc Police Department or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of fee.

Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH.

CONDITION TIME: 10 months, 1st 6 months straight time and the last 4 month with huber. 

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
